{"answer": "Before importing data, you should keep the following in mind: 1. Find and replace any occurrences of sensitive values like "icm", "share-nlb", "QA", "hl", "Cognito", "S3", "ECS", "SG-ID", and "Task-definition (ARN)" to ensure they are updated correctly.
2. Manually validate the correctness of the above values to prevent import or deployment failures.
3. Ensure that NLB URLs, S3 bucket references, Cognito values, VPC, subnets, security groups, and task definition ARNs are all validated and updated as necessary.
4. Validate global properties against project or environment-specific requirements.", "sources": ["s3://document-portal-storage-195932288857/devops/dynamodb-_-ctm-validations-before-import.docx"], "success": true}
